<div class="govuk-grid-column-two-thirds">
    <h1 class="govuk-heading-xl">@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

    <p class="govuk-body">Personal data collected by the FC under the EAPC (or related) system(s) will be held and used in accordance with the requirements of the current data protection legislation.</p>
    <p class="govuk-body">The FC will use the personal information you provide to administer your current and future applications for export phytosanitary certificates. If you do not provide the required information, we will be unable to process your application.</p>
    <p class="govuk-body">This information may be shared with other competent authorities of the UK or with member states in the European Union and Government departments.</p>
    <p class="govuk-body">This information will not be disclosed to other parties except to help prevent fraud and for the prevention and detection of crime or if required to do so by law.</p>
    <p class="govuk-body">As per our terms and conditions, we will hold your information on our systems until you notify us in writing that you would like your information removed (as per our retention policy). We will hold this information securely within the UK or EU.</p>
    <p class="govuk-body">The FC is registered as a data controller under the Data Protection Act 2018 (Registration No: Z6542658). The FC&apos;s Data Protection Officer can be contacted at <a href="mailto:informationrights@forestrycommission.gov.uk">informationrights@forestrycommission.gov.uk</a>.</p>
    <p class="govuk-body">You can read our personal information charter on our website <a target="_blank" class="govuk-link" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="Open the Forestry Commission&apos;s Personal Information Charter" href="https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/forestry-commission/about/personal-information-charter">https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/forestry-commission/about/personal-information-charter (opens in new tab)</a></p>
    <p class="govuk-body">You have a number of rights under the Data Protection Act 2018, listed in full on the Information Commissioner&apos;s website.</p>
    <p class="govuk-body">You have the right to lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority, the Information Commissioners&apos; Office, on their website, <a target="_blank" class="govuk-link" aria-label="Open the Information Commissioner&apos;s Office website" href="https://ico.org.uk/">https://ico.org.uk/ (opens in new tab)</a></p>
</div>